# 📘 IPv4 Subnetting Lab (Packet Tracer)

## 🧠 Overview
This lab demonstrates how to design and implement IPv4 subnetting using a /24 network.

The network is divided into multiple subnets based on host requirements and future scalability.

---

## 🎯 Objectives
- Design a subnetting scheme
- Assign IP addresses to devices
- Configure router and switches
- Verify connectivity using ping

---

## 🧩 Requirements
- LAN-A: ≥ 50 hosts
- LAN-B: ≥ 40 hosts
- At least 2 additional subnets
- Same subnet mask (no VLSM)

---

## 🛠 Solution Summary
- Base network: 192.168.0.0/24
- Chosen subnet mask: /26
- Total subnets: 4
- Hosts per subnet: 62

---

## 📁 Project Structure
- docs/ → Design and explanation
- configs/ → Device configurations
- assets/ → Topology & Packet Tracer file

---

## ✅ Results
- Successful communication between all devices
- All pings passed

---

## 🚀 Skills Demonstrated
- IPv4 subnetting
- Network design
- Cisco CLI configuration
- Troubleshooting connectivity
